{"title":"Chumba Rolls Out SLACKR Geo Along With More Sizes For Sendero and Yaupon","link":"https://theradavist.com/chumba-slackr-geo/","date":1722876897000,"content":"<p><img width=\"1100\" height=\"733\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/Chumba-SLackr-Ti-Hardtail-Detail.jpg\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/Chumba-SLackr-Ti-Hardtail-Detail.jpg?w=1100&amp;quality=75 1100w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/Chumba-SLackr-Ti-Hardtail-Detail.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w\" /></p>\n<p><em><a href=\"https://theradavist.com/?s=Chumba\" target=\"_blank\">Chumba</a>‘s 150 mm travel titanium hardtail, <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/first-look-chumba-slackr-150-mm-titanium-hardtail/\" target=\"_blank\">named the SLACKR</a> after the cult classic film from Austin, TX, <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KlmfRuXxuXo\" target=\"_blank\">Slacker</a>, just got its official geometry. The brand also rolled out new sizes for its <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/chunder-and-chamisa-on-the-chumba-sendero-29er-hardtail/\" target=\"_blank\">Sendero hardtail</a> and Yaupon drop-bar 29er mountain bike. Let’s check it out.</em><span></span></p>\n<p><img width=\"1000\" height=\"669\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/Chumba-SLACKR-GEO-Chart-Diagram.jpg?resize=150,150&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/Chumba-SLACKR-GEO-Chart-Diagram.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/Chumba-SLACKR-GEO-Chart-Diagram.jpg?resize=768,514&amp;quality=75 768w\" /><img width=\"2412\" height=\"1646\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/Chumba-SLACKR-Titanium-GEO.jpg?fit=1200,1646&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/Chumba-SLACKR-Titanium-GEO.jpg?w=2412&amp;quality=75 2412w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/Chumba-SLACKR-Titanium-GEO.jpg?resize=1200,819&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/Chumba-SLACKR-Titanium-GEO.jpg?resize=2000,1365&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/Chumba-SLACKR-Titanium-GEO.jpg?resize=768,524&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/Chumba-SLACKR-Titanium-GEO.jpg?resize=1536,1048&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/Chumba-SLACKR-Titanium-GEO.jpg?resize=2048,1398&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2408\" height=\"1650\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/Chumba-SLACKR-Titanium-GEO-Sagge.jpg?fit=1200,1650&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/Chumba-SLACKR-Titanium-GEO-Sagge.jpg?w=2408&amp;quality=75 2408w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/Chumba-SLACKR-Titanium-GEO-Sagge.jpg?resize=1200,822&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/Chumba-SLACKR-Titanium-GEO-Sagge.jpg?resize=2000,1370&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/Chumba-SLACKR-Titanium-GEO-Sagge.jpg?resize=768,526&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/Chumba-SLACKR-Titanium-GEO-Sagge.jpg?resize=1536,1052&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/Chumba-SLACKR-Titanium-GEO-Sagge.jpg?resize=2048,1403&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p>The SLACKR sports a 64.5º head and 75.2º seat angle unsagged across the small through XL size range and a continuous 53 mm bottom bracket drop, save for the small with 55 mm and XL, which sport a 49 mm drop. What’s impressive is the stack height across all sizes, which is in-line with a 150 mm travel hardtail.</p>\n<p>The Austin, Texas-based bicycle manufacturers have also just released new sizes across all its MTB models as well. With MTB riders planning their builds around a narrow range of short stem lengths (typically 32-60mm), Chumba felt riders could benefit from more subtle changes across model sizes.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2020/06/Chunder-and-Chamisa-on-the-Chumba-Sendero-29er-Hardtail-32.jpg?fit=1200,1333&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2020/06/Chunder-and-Chamisa-on-the-Chumba-Sendero-29er-Hardtail-32.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2020/06/Chunder-and-Chamisa-on-the-Chumba-Sendero-29er-Hardtail-32.jpg?resize=1024,682&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2020/06/Chunder-and-Chamisa-on-the-Chumba-Sendero-29er-Hardtail-32.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2020/06/Chunder-and-Chamisa-on-the-Chumba-Sendero-29er-Hardtail-32.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2020/06/Chunder-and-Chamisa-on-the-Chumba-Sendero-29er-Hardtail-32.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2020/06/Chunder-and-Chamisa-on-the-Chumba-Sendero-29er-Hardtail-32.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2020/06/Chunder-and-Chamisa-on-the-Chumba-Sendero-29er-Hardtail-32.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<ul>\n<li>The <a href=\"https://chumbausa.com/slackr-titanium-mtb-150-140-travel-hardtail\" target=\"_blank\"><em>SLACKR</em></a> is now available in 6 sizes: S, S/M, M, M/L, L, and XL</li>\n<li>The <a href=\"https://chumbausa.com/made-in-usa-mountain-bikes\" target=\"_blank\">Yaupon</a> is now available in 6 sizes: S, S/M, M, M/L, L, and XL</li>\n<li>The <a href=\"https://chumbausa.com/made-in-usa-mountain-bikes\" target=\"_blank\">Sendero</a> is now available in 5 sizes: S, M, M/L, L, and XL</li>\n</ul>\n<p>You can read more on the SLACKR at <a href=\"https://chumbausa.com/blog/2024/7/29/-geometry-posted-new-sizes-added-for-sendero-and-yaupon-models\" target=\"_blank\">Chumba</a> and check out our related content below for all-things Chumba.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/chumba-slackr-geo/\">Chumba Rolls Out SLACKR Geo Along With More Sizes For Sendero and Yaupon</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"c3a7973a729151ff3d22c32781bedee8828501f72b7956a180cf05618006e4aa","category":"Cycling"}